#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012 |title=In The Murmuring Trees  |author=R. Tirrell Leonard Jr.  |page=79 |ISBN=1479730920 |passage=A wrinkle in the '''cloth''' of time, a cry of soft caress and fragrant dreams to weld the metal fabric souls in blends so held in high regards across the lands and sky. }}
